The correct usage of shorthand alt syntax: 
```sqf
[try](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/try) {
	[if](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/if) (a > b) [throw](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/throw) "Error: some error"; *// OK*
	*// The command argument is static*
} catch {
	[hint](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/hint) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) _exception;
};

[try](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/try) {
	_someFunc = {
		.....
	};
	[if](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/if) (a > b) [throw](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/throw) ([call](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/call) _someFunc); *// NOT OK*
	*// The command argument is dynamic*
	*// _someFunc is called first to get the value regardless of (a > b) outcome*
} catch {
	[hint](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/hint) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) _exception;
};

[try](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/try) {
	_someFunc = {
		.....
	};
	[if](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/if) (a > b) [then](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/then) {[throw](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/throw) ([call](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/call) _someFunc)}; /// OK
	*// The command argument is dynamic*
	*// _someFunc is only called when (a > b) is [true](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/true)*
} catch {
	[hint](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/hint) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) _exception;
};
```

