There is no guarantee that spawned scripts will be executed in the same order they spawned: 

```sqf
[for](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/for) "_i" [from](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/from) 0 [to](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/to) 100 [do](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/do) 
{
	_null = _i spawn 
	{
		[diag_log](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/diag_log) _this;
	};
}; *// Result: 51,1,2...49,50,0,52,53...100*
```
Local variables declared in the main scope are not available in the spawned code. You have to pass them as parameters:

```sqf
[private](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/private) _localVariable = 1234;
[_localVariable] spawn 
