with.description:
Creates a [With Type](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/With_Type) that is used inside a [do](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/do) construct in order to execute code inside a given namespace. 
> ⚠when used in a do-construct in scripts with allowed suspension, an unexpected namespace switch could happen (see note below)
**NOTE** for the reasons unknown, namespace switching might unexpectedly occur inside some scopes ([for](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/for), [if](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/if), [try](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/try), [call](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/call)) started in [scheduled](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/Scheduler#Scheduled_Environment) scripts ([canSuspend](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/canSuspend) true) after small suspension if with was not the main scope. For example: 

```sqf
[] [spawn](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/spawn)
{
	with [uiNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/uiNamespace) do 
	{
		[for](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/for) "_i" [from](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/from) 1 [to](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/to) 1 [do](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/do) 
		{
			[systemChat](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/systemChat) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) [
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [uiNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/uiNamespace), 
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [missionNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/missionNamespace)
			]; 
			// result [true, false]
			[sleep](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/sleep) 0.05; //<-- small suspension
			[systemChat](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/systemChat) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) [
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [uiNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/uiNamespace), 
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [missionNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/missionNamespace)
			]; 
			// result [false, true] <-- switching
		};
	};
};
```

However if with used in parent scope, everything works correctly:

```sqf
with [uiNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/uiNamespace) do
{
	[] [spawn](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/spawn) 
	{
		[for](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/for) "_i" [from](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/from) 1 [to](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/to) 1 [do](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/do) 
		{
			[systemChat](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/systemChat) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) [
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [uiNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/uiNamespace), 
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [missionNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/missionNamespace)
			]; 
			// result [true, false]
			[sleep](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/sleep) 0.05; //<-- small suspension
			[systemChat](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/systemChat) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) [
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [uiNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/uiNamespace), 
				[currentNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/currentNamespace) [isEqualTo](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/isEqualTo) [missionNamespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/missionNamespace)
			]; 
			// result [true, false] <-- NO switching
		};
	};
};
```


To eliminate possibility of error you can also use [setVariable](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/setVariable) or [getVariable](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/getVariable) with desired [Namespace](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/Namespace), which is also [scheduled environment](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/Scheduler#Scheduled_Environment) safe.

examples:
```sqf
try {[throw](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/throw) "invalid argument"} [catch](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/catch) {[hint](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/hint) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) _exception};
```
*since Arma 3 v1.53.133045*: 
```sqf
123 try {[if](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/if) (_this != 123) [throw](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/throw) "invalid argument"} [catch](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/catch) {[hint](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/hint) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) _exception};
```
The correct usage of shorthand alt syntax: 
```sqf
try {
	[if](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/if) (a > b) [throw](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/throw) "Error: some error"; *// OK*
	*// The command argument is static*
} [catch](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/catch) {
	[hint](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/hint) [str](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/str) _exception;
};

try {
	_someFunc = {
		.....
	};
	[if](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/if) (a > b) [throw](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/throw) ([call](https://community.bistudio.com/wiki/call) _someFunc); *// NOT OK*
	*// The command argument is dynamic*
